SIMPLE: redeemable
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Redeemable
<hw>Re*deem"a*ble</hw> <pr>(-?*b;l)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Capable of being redeemed; subject to repurchase; held under
conditions permitting redemption; <as>as, a pledge securing the payment
of money is <ex>redeemable</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Subject to an obligation of redemption; conditioned
upon a promise of redemption; payable; due; <as>as, bonds, promissory
notes, etc.</as> , <xex>redeemable</xex> in gold, or in current money,
or four months after date.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Redeemableness</ent>⟦br⟧
